National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has donated N50m to Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Niger State. He made the donation on Thursday during a condolence visit to Governor Abubakar Sani-Bello over the spate of killings by bandits in Niger State.   BREAKING: Niger Gov backs Tinubu for 2023 presidency     Abia Court ruling vindicates Kanu â€“ IPOB     Obi Cubana meets Lagos hawker, restates scholarship offer   Making the donation to the Governor at the Government House in Minna, Tinubu said that it was to help alleviate the suffering of the people who have been affected by the banditry attacks in the State. He stated that the current government was doing its best in fighting banditry, adding that the incoming government would eliminate the bandits and terrorists and put an end to their activities.